==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Millilitre
<hw>Mil"li*li`tre</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>millilitre</ets>;
<ets>milli-</ets> milli- + <ets>litre</ets>. See <er>Liter</er>.]</ety>
<def>A measure of capacity in the metric system, containing the
thousandth part of a liter. It is very nearly equal to a cubic
centimeter, and is equal to .061025 of an English cubic inch, or to
.033815 of an American fluid ounce.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

